title: Find this site: Someone built a personal 'tinder' (with reward incentive)?
text:
Hey HN, I'm trying to find this old website (created at least 4 years ago), can you help?

This guy created a site where you could nominate your friends to become friends (maybe romantic partner, I don't remember) with the creator. It began with a bio of himself and the nomination form without much else.

The promise was for any nominator of a "successful" candidate, they (both?) would receive some cash award ($500, or something).

I believe there may have also been an article written about the experience.

I hope you find it... GLHF :)

Ask HN: Give me feedback on my idea please “VSCO, but for video”
text:
I enjoy using VSCO since it's a place where I can find awesome photos without all the BS noise that Instagram has. However, I don't like how I need to pay $25 per year to be able to publish videos/edit videos. This led me to my idea.

I want to create an app that is like VSCO, but for video. The app would give you video editing tools, and it would be free. It wouldn't have comments, and the followers/likes wouldn't be public, therefore you won't feel social pressure when posting. The revenue model would be advertising, people can "boost" their posts to get more eyeballs, similar to how Twitter allows their users to boost their tweets.

I want this app to be a place where people can edit and upload their videos to share with their friends, without the social pressure of likes/comments/followers (the numbers game).

What do you guys think?
